Token.description:
JWT access token response model.

**Backward Compatibility** (v1.0 → v1.1):
- Added `email_verified` field in v1.1
- Old clients (v1.0): Ignore this field, continue as before
- New clients (v1.1+): Check this field and show UI reminders if false

**Feature Flag**: ENFORCE_EMAIL_VERIFICATION
- false (default): Soft enforcement, unverified users CAN login
- true: Strict enforcement, unverified users blocked with 403

**Client Handling Example**:
```typescript
// Old clients (v1.0) - No changes needed
const { access_token } = response;
localStorage.setItem('token', access_token);

// New clients (v1.1+) - Handle verification status
const { access_token, email_verified } = response;
localStorage.setItem('token', access_token);
if (!email_verified) {
  showBanner("Please verify your email for full access");
}
```
